<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-ninth session 
</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
</b></p>
<p><b>political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
</b></p>
<p><b>including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Pakistan: amendment to draft resolution A/HRC/29/L.25 
</b></p>
<p><b>29</b>/&#8230;<b>Protection of the family: contribution of the family to the 
realization of the right to an adequate standard of living for its 
</b></p>
<p><b>members, particularly through its role in poverty eradication and 
</b></p>
<p><b>achieving sustainable development 
</b></p>
<p> After paragraph 4, insert a new paragraph <i>reading</i> 
</p>
<p>4 bis. <i>Recognizes</i> that men and women of full age, without any limitation due to 
</p>
<p>race, nationality or religion, have the rights to marry and to found a family, bearing in mind 
</p>
<p>that marriage is a union between a man and a woman; 
</p>
